ntake replacing the WPS front door.", "threat_level": "dormant"}]}, "champion_strength": {"source": "Pricing Structure call, 25 Jun 2026; Avoma Zycus Onsite Teil 1 and Teil 2, 1 Jul 2026", "at_risk": false, "summary": "P\u00f6lki (project co-lead and strategic buyer) and Karin Eppich (system-side lead), with Melissa Koller, are actively pushing internally to lock Zycus in; on 25 Jun P\u00f6lki called the current move their lifeline to secure the deal. They advocate strongly but cannot commit budget or IT resources, so the missing piece is an ROI case and an IT-resource story to carry upward.", "champion": "Karin Eppich", "strength": "strong"}, "stakeholder_map": {"items": [{"name": "Engelbert P\u00f6lki", "risk": "cannot commit budget or IT resources himself; needs air cover upward", "role": "Decision Maker", "email": "engelbert.poelki@post.at", "title": "Manager Strategic Projects IT & Supply Chain", "_source": "sfdc_contact_role", "sentiment": "positive", "_matched_ai": true, "last_contact_date": "2026-07-01"}, {"name": "Karin Eppich", "risk": "system-side focus; limited commercial authority", "role": "Champion", "email": "karin.eppich@post.at", "title": "Purchasing processes and systems", "_source": "sfdc_contact_role", "sentiment": "positive", "_matched_ai": true, "last_contact_date": "2026-07-01"}, {"name": "KOLLER Melissa", "risk": "solution lands in her team; needs the P2P/procurement phase to stay in scope", "role": "Influencer", "email": "melissa.koller@post.at", "title": "Head of Purchasing Procure2Pay", "_source": "sfdc_contact_role", "sentiment": "positive", "_matched_ai": true, "last_contact_date": "2026-07-01"}, {"name": "DERNITZKY Markus", "risk": "technical owner tasked with WPS API checks; integration verdict rides on him", "role": "Influencer", "email": "markus.dernitzky@post.at", "title": "NA", "_source": "sfdc_contact_role", "sentiment": "neutral", "_matched_ai": true, "last_contact_date": "2026-07-01"}, {"name": "OSTERKORN Karina", "risk": "finance/budget path not yet engaged by Zycus", "role": "Influencer", "email": "karina.osterkorn@post.at", "title": "Head of Staff Unit Projects Finance", "_source": "sfdc_contact_role", "sentiment": "neutral", "_matched_ai": true}, {"name": "Manfred Tauner", "role": "Influencer", "email": "manfred.tauner@post.at", "title": "Corporate Category Manager Transporte & Frachten", "_source": "sfdc_contact_role", "_role_inferred": true}, {"name": "Bernd Schaller", "role": "Decision Maker", "email": "bernd.schaller@post.at", "title": "Head of Strategic Procurement for Energy & Services", "_source": "sfdc_contact_role", "_role_inferred": true}]}, "meddpicc": {"metrics": {"status": "partial", "sources": ["Avoma Zycus Onsite Teil 2, 1 Jul 2026", "Pricing Structure call, 25 Jun 2026"], "narrative": "The value story is qualitative, not quantified. The group procurement lead was explicit on 1 Jul that Austrian Post is already highly digitalized and therefore 'there is no real sense of urgency to change everything', and that the business cases 'are fighting against each other' for internal budget, so procurement must prove value to rank the investment. Group spend is about 1 billion EUR across roughly 35 procurement staff, and the upside is AI/agentic automation plus a unified S2P suite replacing the aging WPS landscape, but no ROI, savings, or cycle-time numbers have been put on the table. Quantifying the business case is the highest-value MEDDPICC action."}, "champion": {"status": "confirmed", "sources": ["Pricing Structure call, 25 Jun 2026", "SF Next_Step (Eppich preference, 16 Mar 2026)", "Avoma Zycus Onsite Teil 1, 1 Jul 2026"], "narrative": "There is a strong internal champion network. P\u00f6lki, the strategic buyer and project co-lead, described the current move as 'unser Strohhalm von der Melissa, von der Karin und von mir, dass wir das Ding hier einfangen k\u00f6nnen' (25 Jun), i.e. he, Karin Eppich and Melissa Koller are actively trying to lock Zycus in. Karin Eppich (system-side project lead) expressed a preference for Zycus on 16 Mar and drives the technical workstream. What is still missing is not advocacy but air cover: the champions cannot commit budget or IT resources, so they need Zycus to arm them with an ROI case and an IT-resource story to carry upward."}, "competition": {"status": "partial", "sources": ["Avoma Zycus Onsite Teil 1, 1 Jul 2026", "Pricing Structure call, 25 Jun 2026", "POC feedback call, 11 Jun 2026"], "narrative": "This is a live head-to-head with Coupa: on 1 Jul the Zycus rep noted the buyer had run similar API/integration conversations with Coupa, and on 25 Jun the rep characterized it as a 'Kopf-an-Kopf-Rennen' where Coupa also turns flexible on commercials. Zycus leads on function and AI per the 11 Jun POC feedback, and is inside the stated budget, so the wedge is commercial flexibility plus the agentic-AI edge, not features. GEP is on the shortlist but invisible on calls, and an orchestration-overlay path (Tronkeon-style bolt-on to avoid SAP effort) tempts IT. The single strongest current threat is not a rival vendor but do-nothing/deferral driven by the IT resource gate and an internal budget fight, made sharper by the board putting its biggest logistics project on hold."}, "identify_pain": {"status": "confirmed", "sources": ["Avoma Zycus Onsite Teil 1 and Teil 2, 1 Jul 2026", "System demo, 19 May 2025"], "narrative": "The confirmed pain is an aging, fragmented procurement landscape: the incumbent WPS / Allocation Network P2P (acquired by QAT) has poor post-acquisition support and the buyer is on an older WPS4 build, with the buying team surprised by how far behind it sits. The buyer wants one interconnected S2P suite with AI and a partner that brings use-case ideas, and it wants to eliminate its separate procurement information system, which Zycus S2C can replace. The countervailing reality, stated by the group procurement lead, is that high existing digitalization means urgency is low, so the pain own